# 1. Encoded PowerShell Execution

## Objective

Simulate obfuscated PowerShell execution commonly used by attackers to evade detection, execute malicious scripts, or deliver payloads.

## Attack Technique

Attackers frequently use Base64-encoded PowerShell commands to hide malicious activity from security tools and administrators.

## MITRE ATT&CK

- T1059.001 — PowerShell
- T1027 — Obfuscated Files or Information

## Simulation Performed

Executed PowerShell using the `-EncodedCommand` and `-enc` parameters to trigger Sysmon process creation telemetry.

## Detection Result

Microsoft Sentinel generated a High severity incident based on Sysmon Event ID 1 process creation logs.

## Detection Triggered

- Encoded PowerShell Execution
